just_use GestureArbitration.elm

# label: WORKHORSE (gesture-arbitration)
# role: pure helpers — click-vs-drag arbitration during board interactions

Pure-function port of the click-vs-drag arbitration logic from
TS's `DragDropHelper` (`angry-cat/src/lyn_rummy/game/game.ts`,
lines 2475-2672). Nothing in this module touches the DOM; the
event flow itself lives in `Main.elm`.

## What's exported

- `Point` — `{ x : Int, y : Int }` (viewport coords).
- `clickThreshold : Int` — squared-distance threshold above
  which click intent dies. Direct port of TS literal `1`.
- `distSquared : Point -> Point -> Int` — Euclidean squared
  distance.
- `clickIntentAfterMove : Point -> Point -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int`
  — given the original cursor, the current cursor, and the
  current click intent, return the new click intent. Nothing
  stays Nothing (death is permanent within a gesture); Just
  survives iff cursor displacement is `<= clickThreshold`.
- `applySplit : Int -> Int -> List CardStack -> List CardStack`
  — replace the stack at `stackIndex` with the two halves
  produced by `CardStack.split cardIndex`. No-op on out-of-
  bounds, on empty board, and on 1-card stacks (CardStack.split
  preserves them).

## Why this exists

Without this module, the arbitration logic would live entirely
in `Main.elm`'s `update`, where elm-test can't reach it.
Pulling the pure pieces into a named module gives us 21 unit
tests over thresholds and split semantics
(`tests/LynRummy/GestureArbitrationTest.elm`) — most of the
behavior worth verifying about the arbitration is verifiable
here without booting a browser.

## Concession (preserved from TS, by design)

The TS click UI is not optimal. A user who jitters more than
1 pixel between mousedown and mouseup turns their click into
a drag. Steve knows this; the rule is "port it faithfully
first, improve after the rest of the port lands." See
`showell/claude_writings/the_bar_for_done.md`.

## Pointers

- Consumer: `Main.elm` (update branches for `MouseDownOnBoardCard`,
  `MouseMove`, `MouseUp`).
- TS reference: `DragDropHelper.enable_drag` and the surrounding
  closure-captured state machine (`active_click_key`,
  `dist_squared`, `process_pointerup`).
- Maintainer-doc essay: `showell/claude_writings/reading_dragdrophelper.md`.
- Plan essay: `showell/claude_writings/splitting_a_stack.md`.
